docs.title: Introduction
docs.text: Write a brief introduction to introduce the topic and the image.

docs.title: Section 1: Exploring the Image
docs.text: Describe the content of the image and its relevance to the topic.

docs.title: Section 2: Analysis
docs.text: Provide an analysis of the image's significance, context, and any relevant details.

docs.title: Subsection 2.1: Visual Elements
docs.text: Discuss specific visual elements within the image, such as colors, shapes, and composition.

docs.title: Subsection 2.2: Interpretation
docs.text: Offer your interpretation of what the image represents or symbolizes in relation to the subject matter.

docs.title: Section 3: Comparisons
docs.text: Compare the image with other relevant visuals, concepts, or examples.

docs.title: Conclusion
docs.text: Summarize the insights gained from analyzing the image and its connection to the broader topic.

docs.title: References
docs.text: List any sources, references, or citations, including the source of the image if applicable.
